summary:
Tumor depth is an important factor in soft tissue sarcoma prognostication because it reflects local invasiveness and contributes to predicting local recurrence and poor survival, especially in specific subtypes such as leiomyosarcoma. It is consistently incorporated into established prognostic tools like the Memorial Sloan Kettering nomogram, supporting its role even when other factors are stronger overall predictors. 

\boxed{A}

